---
// /industries/ — universal industry hub (Phase 5, 2026-05-04)
// Demotes the 5 vertical landers to one of many; signals breadth
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Industries we serve | Agni AI Store"
  description="The same lifecycle playbook fits every owner-operated service business. Five industries with deep playbooks live now &mdash; vet, chiro/physio, dental, med-spa, HVAC. Many more we serve. The audit tells you if your shape fits."
>
  <section class="ai-hero">
    <p class="ai-eyebrow">INDUSTRIES</p>
    <h1>Same playbook. <br>Different vocabulary, software, and rules.</h1>
    <p class="ai-lead">
      The four leaks &mdash; phone, dormancy, response time, review velocity &mdash; show up in every owner-operated service business we&rsquo;ve audited. The playbook is universal. What changes is the vocabulary (recall vs reactivation vs rebooking), the software (AVImark vs Jane vs Open Dental vs ServiceTitan), and the regulator (CVO vs CCO vs HRAI vs the dental colleges). We&rsquo;ve built deep playbooks for five industries. We&rsquo;ll tell you on the audit if yours fits.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="ai-section">
    <div class="ai-wrap">
      <p class="ai-eyebrow" style="text-align:center;">Lead playbooks</p>
      <h2 style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:32px;">Five industries with vertical-specific implementations.</h2>
      <div class="ai-vertical-strip">

        <a class="ai-vertical-card" href="/for-vets/">
          <h3>Vet clinics</h3>
          <p>Recall, lapsed-client win-back, after-hours calls, CVO/AVMA-compliant review automation. Wraps around AVImark, Cornerstone, ezyVet, Vetspire, Covetrus.</p>
          <span class="ai-vertical-card-arrow">For vet clinics &rarr;</span>
        </a>

        <a class="ai-vertical-card" href="/for-chiros/">
          <h3>Chiro &amp; physio</h3>
          <p>Reactivation, 5-minute lead response, care-plan completion, College-compliant review velocity. Jane App&ndash;native. HIPAA BAA on request.</p>
          <span class="ai-vertical-card-arrow">For chiro &amp; physio &rarr;</span>
        </a>

        <a class="ai-vertical-card" href="/for-dental/">
          <h3>Dental</h3>
          <p>Hygiene recall, dormant-patient reactivation, treatment-plan completion, post-op review velocity. Wraps around Open Dental, Dentrix, ClearDent, Curve.</p>
          <span class="ai-vertical-card-arrow">For dental &rarr;</span>
        </a>

        <a class="ai-vertical-card" href="/for-medspa/">
          <h3>Med-spa &amp; aesthetic</h3>
          <p>Membership reactivation, missed-consultation rescue, package upsell sequences, before/after review automation. Wraps around Boulevard, Aesthetics Pro, Vagaro.</p>
          <span class="ai-vertical-card-arrow">For med-spa &rarr;</span>
        </a>

        <a class="ai-vertical-card" href="/for-hvac/">
          <h3>HVAC &amp; home services</h3>
          <p>In-season missed-call rescue, service-agreement attach, post-job review automation, shoulder-season fill. Wraps around ServiceTitan, Housecall Pro, Jobber.</p>
          <span class="ai-vertical-card-arrow">For HVAC &rarr;</span>
        </a>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="ai-section">
    <div class="ai-wrap">
      <p class="ai-eyebrow" style="text-align:center;">Other industries we serve</p>
      <h2 style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:8px;">Same operational shape. Adjacent verticals.</h2>
      <p style="text-align:center;color:var(--tx-soft);margin-bottom:32px;max-width:680px;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;">
        We&rsquo;ve audited or run engagements for businesses in all of the verticals below. The lifecycle playbook fits. The vocabulary changes. The audit tells us &mdash; and tells you &mdash; whether the dollar impact is worth running.
      </p>
      <div class="ai-grid-3">
        <div class="ai-card">
          <h3>Health-adjacent</h3>
          <p style="color:var(--tx-soft);">Optometry &middot; Mental-health practices &middot; Counsellors &middot; Dietitians &middot; Speech &amp; OT clinics &middot; Audiology</p>
        </div>
        <div class="ai-card">
          <h3>Professional services</h3>
          <p style="color:var(--tx-soft);">Small-firm legal (consumer / family / PI) &middot; Accounting &amp; bookkeeping &middot; Immigration consultants &middot; Real-estate teams</p>
        </div>
        <div class="ai-card">
          <h3>Personal care &amp; hospitality</h3>
          <p style="color:var(--tx-soft);">Salons &amp; spas &middot; Barbershops &middot; Pet grooming, boarding, daycare &middot; Independent restaurants (host/reservations side)</p>
        </div>
        <div class="ai-card">
          <h3>Education &amp; coaching</h3>
          <p style="color:var(--tx-soft);">Tutoring centres &middot; Independent music schools &middot; Driving schools &middot; Group fitness &amp; yoga &amp; pilates studios</p>
        </div>
        <div class="ai-card">
          <h3>Trades &amp; home services</h3>
          <p style="color:var(--tx-soft);">Plumbing &middot; Electrical &middot; Roofing &middot; Landscaping &middot; Cleaning &middot; Pest control &middot; Garage door &middot; Pool &amp; spa</p>
        </div>
        <div class="ai-card">
          <h3>Specialty fitness</h3>
          <p style="color:var(--tx-soft);">Climbing gyms &middot; Boxing/MMA studios &middot; Crossfit &middot; Pilates &middot; Specialty cycling &middot; Recovery studios</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="ai-section">
    <div class="ai-wrap ai-narrow" style="text-align:center;">
      <h2>Don&rsquo;t see your industry?</h2>
      <p class="ai-lead">Book the audit. If the four leaks apply, the playbook applies. If it doesn&rsquo;t fit, we&rsquo;ll tell you on the call &mdash; and you keep the report.</p>
      <div class="ai-cta-row">
        <a class="ai-btn" href="https://calendly.com/aman-shopagni" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Book the audit &rarr;</a>
        <a class="ai-btn-ghost" href="/engagements/">Engagement shapes</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
